## Constraints

- Every verification must produce evidence (command output, file paths, line numbers).
- If any check fails, report the specific failure with remediation steps.
- Depth test must be applied honestly — shallow modules must be flagged.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Preserve the original prompt structure and formatting.
- Handle missing variables gracefully (leave as-is or use default if specified).

